Description: The first completely AI powered career and skills development playground built for talented self starter employees.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Skill.me is the skills app that stops employees jumping from company to company. Skill.me makes employees happy because it demonstrates to employees that the “Company cares about their Careers”. At Microsoft 15,000 team members using Skill.me recorded the highest ever employee satisfaction ratings for “My Manager Cares about My Career”. Using Skill.me employees manage skills using Kanban style boards personalized with the skills that drive success in the role they perform or for the project, gig they are engaged in. Using skill boards employees can easily identify skill proficiency levels, skill gaps and prioritize skills for development all with suggestions from managers.  Based on skills prioritized employees find pre-qualified experts to help accelerate skill development through “Perfect Matching”. Skill.me uniquely matches experts from inside of the company and outside of the company, ensuring the right experts are perfectly matched. Skill.me matches bi-directionally, meaning employees are matched with the right experts and experts are matched with the right employees. “Perfect Matching” at scale across global communities leads to accelerated skill development.  With Skill.me knowledge is power, managers are provided with insights to help them match their teams with the right skill priorities and address the most important skill gaps and L&D are provided with insight that ensures they develop skill development programs targeting at addressing the most significant skill gaps from across the company.   ChatGTP is the perfect skilling mate. ChatGTP is fully integrated into Skill.me meaning employees can use ChatGTP to find new skills for upskilling and reskilling. Its easy for employees to ask questions like “What are the top soft skills for my role?” and these skills will be added to employee’s skill boards. ChatGTP finds the very best courses, talks, articles, and masterclasses and matches them with the skills prioritized for development by every employee. Skill.me uses the power of AI to deliver a completely personalized learning experience for every employee demonstrating that the company truly “Cares about my career”.  By combining the no:1 Skills App for Microsoft Teams with the no:1 AI platform Skill.me personalizes learning at scale and with a level of precision never seen before, leading to more satisfied employees, higher employee retention rates and business growth strategies that for the first time are truly people led.

Description: Federal Election Commission is focused on the administration and enforcement of the Federal Election Campaign Act.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: Federal Election Commission is focused on the administration and enforcement of the Federal Election Campaign Act, which is the statute governing the financing of federal elections.  The organization’s duties include disclosing campaign finance information, enforcing the provisions of the law such as the limits and prohibitions on contributions, and to oversee the public funding of the presidential elections. The commission is made up of 6 members who serve a six year term, with two of these seats subjected to appointment every two years. By law, no more than three Commissioners can be members of the same political party, and at least four votes are required for any official Commission action. This structure was created to encourage non-partisan decisions. The chairmanship of the commission rotates among the members each year, with no member serving as chairman more than once during his or her term. Federal Election Commission was formed in 1975 and is headquartered in Washington, D.C., United States.
Industry Groups: Government and Military, Other, Privacy and Security, Professional Services

The Company also provides the FAMILION family of genetic tests for inherited cardiac syndromes, including cardiac channelopathies and cardiomyopathies. Full Description: Liz Claiborne is a fashion portal that designs and markets a wide range of women's and men's apparel, accessories and fragrance products under the Kate Spade New York, Kate Spade Saturday, and Jack Spade labels. Liz Claiborne Inc. was founded in 1976 by Liz Claiborne, Art Ortenberg, Leonard Boxer, and Jerome Chazen. It was an immediate success with sales of $2 million in 1976 and $23 million in 1978. In 1980, Nina McLemore founded Liz Claiborne Accessories. Liz Claiborne Inc. went public in 1981 and had made the Fortune 500 in 1986, ten years after it was founded, with retail sales of $1.2 billion. It was the first company founded by a woman to be listed in the Fortune 500.
